Here’s everything I am doing for results-
no fancy tricks, just basic habits that I am following seriously:

	1.	Cardio every single day:
Even when I didn’t feel like it, I pushed myself to move. Whether it was running, walking, or a quick HIIT session — I made sure I got my heart rate up daily. No excuses!

	2.	Drinking LOTS of water:
Trust me, staying hydrated made a big difference. It helped me control unnecessary hunger, made my skin better, and kept my energy levels up.

	3.	Following a 1500 calorie diet strictly:
I tracked every meal, every snack. It wasn’t about starving, it was about eating the right amount. I made sure I was in a calorie deficit, but still getting all the nutrients I needed.

	4.	Adding fiber to every meal:
Fiber kept me full for longer. I added fruits, veggies, and whole grains to every plate. It helped my digestion and also reduced those random hunger cravings.

	5.	Switching junk with healthy alternatives:
I used to crave sweets and sodas, but I found smart replacements. Like protein bars, natural sweet snacks, flavored zero-calorie drinks, or just fruits — way better and guilt-free!

	6.	Sleeping for at least 7 hours daily:
This is so underrated! Proper sleep helped my body recover, kept my mood stable, and made it easier to stick to my routine the next day.

I am not doing anything crazy or extreme — I am just staying consistent.
If I can do it, so can you.
Your dream body isn’t built in a week — it’s built step by step, day by day.
